Titolo: Brain Strainers

Anno: 1983

Descrizione: Brain Strainers is a music video game released for the Atari 8-bit family and Commodore 64 in 1983 and  ColecoVision in 1984. It contains two sub-games, one of which is a clone of the popular 1970s audio game, Simon. It is notable for being one of the earliest music video games to employ pitch-based gameplay in the Clef Climber portion of the game.